<sect3 id="general-options">
<title>Running  Options</title>
<informalexample>
<para>
Settings => Preferences => General => Options
</para>
</informalexample>
<para>
The dialog gives an interface to set some useful general running options, arranged in five broad areas:
<itemizedlist>
	 <listitem><para><link linkend="options-startup">Start Up Actions</link></para></listitem>
	  <listitem><para><link linkend="options-exit">Exit Actions</link></para></listitem>
	 <listitem><para><link linkend="options-timeout">Timeouts</link></para></listitem> 
	 <listitem><para><link linkend="options-incoming">Incoming</link></para></listitem>
	  <listitem><para><link linkend="options-outgoing">Outgoing</link></para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>

<sect4  id="options-startup">
<title>Startup</title>
<para>The top left section of the dialog contains two "toggles" . If you want &app; to check for mail automatically at startup and load all mailboxes check the appropriate button.
</para>
</sect4>

<sect4 id="options-exit">
<title>Exit</title>
<para>On the top right hand side of the preferences dialog you find a toggle for actions to take when &app; shuts down. Currently there is only the choice to empty the garbage or not.
</para>
<para>Select this button to clean out deleted mail from the garbage mailbox. </para>
</sect4>

<sect4 id="options-timeout">
<title>Timeouts</title>
<para>The Timeouts Section of the preferences dialog contains two small scrollable entry areas. These are for setting the length of time &app; will wait before:</para>

	    <para>Marking any selected mail as having been read.</para>
	    <para>Checking any active, configured accounts for new mail.</para>


</sect4>

